## Hexagonal Architecture (Ports & Adapters)

This project uses hexagonal architecture:

- **Core (domain)** — Pure business logic; no framework or I/O dependencies
- **Ports** — Interfaces (input ports: use cases; output ports: repositories/services)
- **Adapters** — Concrete implementations: HTTP controllers, database repos, CLI, message queues

### Rules

- The core never imports adapters; adapters import the core
- Input ports define use cases as interfaces; primary adapters (HTTP, CLI) drive them
- Output ports define repository/service contracts; secondary adapters (DB, HTTP clients) implement them
- All adapter code lives outside `domain/`; inject via constructor or DI container
- Test the core without any adapters using in-memory implementations of output ports
